  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6553 sitting just above the massive -20B gamma wall at 6550, dealers are in aggressive buy mode as they hedge their short gamma exposure in this BREAKOUT regime. The cluster of heavy negative gamma from 6530-6550 creates a dangerous amplification zone where any downside move will trigger intense dealer buying, while the positive gamma wall at 6580 acts as resistance where dealers will sell into strength. The recent GEX surge combined with -26.6% and -42% declines in gamma suggests we're seeing rapid position adjustments that could fuel volatile two-way action.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect wild swings between 6550 support and 6580 resistance as dealers amplify every move.",
